==== 刑事调查 ====
{{main|{{en-link|与本杰明·内塔尼亚胡有关的调查|Investigations involving Benjamin Netanyahu}}}}
自2017年1月以来，以色列警方对内塔尼亚胡进行了调查和质询，案件由“案件1000”和“案件2000”组成，由于他们之间的联系而被警方以这种方式命名。 在第一个案例“1000”中，总理被怀疑涉嫌从商人那里获得不适当的大规模福利，包括好莱坞制片人[[艾農·米爾臣|艾農·米爾臣]]和{{Tsl|en|James Packer}}。<ref>{{cite news |author=[[美联社|美联社]] |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/01/06/netanyahu-questioned-israeli-police-second-time-graft-probe |title=Netanyahu questioned by Israeli police for a second time in graft probe |trans-title=内塔尼亚胡第二次受到以色列警方的贿调查 |newspaper=[[每日电讯报|The Daily Telegraph]] |language=en-GB |date=2017-01-06 |accessdate=2019-03-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190325110801/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/01/06/netanyahu-questioned-israeli-police-second-time-graft-probe/ |archive-date=2019-03-25 |dead-url=no }}</ref> 第二起案件涉嫌与[[新消息报|新消息报]]达成协议，以促进立法削弱新消息报的主要竞争对手{{Tsl|en|Israel Hayom|以色列Hayom}}，以换取新消息报对内塔尼亚胡更有利的报道。<ref>{{cite news |author=TOI staff (Times of Israel员工) |url=https://www.timesofisrael.com/netanyahu-in-secret-talks-with-publisher-named-hostile-journalists-he-wanted-sidelined |title=Netanyahu, in secret talks with publisher, named ‘hostile’ journalists he wanted sidelined |trans-title=内塔尼亚胡在与出版商的秘密会谈中，将他想要解雇的“敌对”记者命名为 |newspaper=The Times of Israel |language=en |date=2017-01-14 |accessdate=2019-03-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190420053548/https://www.timesofisrael.com/netanyahu-in-secret-talks-with-publisher-named-hostile-journalists-he-wanted-sidelined/ |archive-date=2019-04-20 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=Eliyahu Kamisher |url=https://www.jpost.com/Israel-News/Benjamin-Netanyahu/Report-Investigation-of-Netanyahu-to-continue-for-at-least-two-months-485989 |title=Report: Investigation of netanyahu to continue for at least two months |trans-title=报告：调查内塔尼亚胡至少持续两个月 |newspaper=[[耶路撒冷邮报|The Jerusalem Post]] |language=en |date=2017-04-03 |accessdate=2019-03-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180104070038/http://www.jpost.com/Israel-News/Benjamin-Netanyahu/Report-Investigation-of-Netanyahu-to-continue-for-at-least-two-months-485989 |archive-date=2018-01-04 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

